<!-- 002 — SAFE TOOL: Translate This Letter -->
<section class="home-tool" id="home-tool">
  <div class="home-tool-inner">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">SAFE Tools — 002</p>
      <h2>Translate this <em>letter</em>.</h2>
      <p class="tool-lead">Paste any official letter you've been scared to open — a Section 21 from your landlord, a Universal Credit decision, a college exclusion, a debt collector, a court summons. We'll explain it in plain English, pull out the dates, tell you what to do, and who to call for free help. Nothing is stored.</p>
      <a class="tool-cta" href="translate-letter.html">Open the translator →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="home-tool-demo">
      <span class="badge">Example output</span>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px"><strong>Letter type:</strong> Section 21 eviction notice</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px"><strong>What this is saying:</strong> Your landlord is asking you to leave by 25 August. They cannot lawfully evict you before that date and must apply to court if you don't leave.</p>
      <p style="margin:0"><strong>Watch out for:</strong> Two months' notice is the legal minimum. Don't leave the property before this date.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

